    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Consisting of or bounded by curved lines as opposed to straight lines. For furniture pieces having fronts with alternating concave and convex curves, use "serpentine (shape)." For arches or moldings composed of flowing, wavelike curves, use "undulating."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000093795/Encyclopedia Britannica Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000114707/Oxford English Dictionary Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Compuesto de, o definido por líneas curvas. En relación a piezas de mobiliario, los frontis de los que tienen alternativamente líneas cóncavos y convexas, use "serpentina (forma)”. Para otras características tales como arcos y molduras compuestas de curvas fluidas semejantes a olas, use "ondulante”.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Bestaand uit of begrensd door gebogen lijnen. Gebruik 'kronkelend' met betrekking tot meubelstukken waarvan de voorkanten afwisselend concave en convexe lijnen vertonen. Gebruik 'golvend' voor andere kenmerken, zoals bogen of lijstwerken, die bestaan uit vloeiende, golvende rondingen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052374/Polytechnisch woordenboek En-Ne (1991)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>以弧形線條組成或界定的形狀。對於以凸面曲線及凹面曲線交替變化的傢俱前沿而言，使用「蛇狀的 (形狀)」一詞。對於其他特別裝飾，如以流線形及波浪狀曲線組成的拱形或簷板，使用「波狀起伏的」一詞。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
